---
// Buy, Borrow, Die: How Billionaires Pay 0% Forever
import { ShoppingCart, Landmark, Skull, Rocket } from 'lucide-astro';
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="section-line bg-red-500 mb-6"></div>
    <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight mb-3">
      Buy, Borrow, Die: How Billionaires Pay 0% Forever
    </h2>
    <p class="font-body text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      This isn't a conspiracy theory. It's a legal tax strategy that's openly discussed in wealth management circles — and completely unavailable to you.
    </p>

    <!-- The Three Steps -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <ShoppingCart class="w-8 h-8 text-red-600" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">BUY</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Buy appreciating assets (stocks, real estate). <strong>No tax on unrealized gains.</strong> Your wealth grows tax-free as long as you don't sell.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <Landmark class="w-8 h-8 text-red-600" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">BORROW</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Borrow against your assets at 1-3% interest. <strong>Loan proceeds aren't taxable income.</strong> Live on borrowed money, never sell.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <Skull class="w-8 h-8 text-red-600" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">DIE</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          When you die, heirs receive "stepped-up basis." <strong>All gains are wiped out for tax purposes.</strong> They inherit tax-free.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Musk Example -->
    <div class="card p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-gray-100 mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <Rocket class="w-8 h-8 text-red-600" />
        <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900">
          Elon Musk: Buy, Borrow, Die in Action
        </h4>
      </div>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
        SEC filings show Musk has <strong>236 million Tesla shares pledged as collateral</strong> for personal loans — about 1/3 of his holdings, worth ~$82 billion. He borrows billions against these shares from Morgan Stanley, Goldman Sachs, and Bank of America at rock-bottom rates while his stock continues to appreciate tax-free.
      </p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded-xl text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-red-600">$82B</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">In shares pledged</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded-xl text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-red-600">1-3%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Interest rate</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded-xl text-center">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-red-600">$0</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Capital gains paid</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400">
        IFR / SEC Tesla Proxy Statement 2024-2025
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- You vs Them -->
    <div class="card p-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-3">If YOU Need $100K</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2 font-body text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-500 mt-1">•</span>
              <span>Pay yourself income, get taxed 35-45%</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-500 mt-1">•</span>
              <span>Sell assets, pay capital gains 15-20%</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-red-500 mt-1">•</span>
              <span>Take out business loan, pay 8-12% interest</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-4 font-mono text-red-600 font-bold">Net cost: $15,000-$45,000</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-3">If a BILLIONAIRE Needs $100M</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2 font-body text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-500 mt-1">•</span>
              <span>Borrow against stock, no tax event</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-500 mt-1">•</span>
              <span>Pay 1-3% interest to banks</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-blue-500 mt-1">•</span>
              <span>Stock keeps appreciating, still no tax</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-4 font-mono text-blue-600 font-bold">Net cost: $1M-$3M (1-3%)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="text-center mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100">
        <p class="font-body text-lg text-gray-700">
          <strong>You pay your full tax rate.</strong> They borrow tax-free, their heirs inherit tax-free. Same country, completely different systems.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">
          ProPublica 2021: Top 25 billionaires paid average 3.4% true tax rate
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
